Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at an event celebrating Small Business Week. She praised small-business owners as the backbone of the American economy and emphasized President Biden's commitment to supporting them. Harris shared her personal experience with a small-business owner who played a significant role in her life. She highlighted the important role small-business owners play in their communities and the opportunities they create. The Vice President discussed the resources and support the administration is providing to help small-business owners, such as investing in community banks and forming public-private partnerships. Harris concluded by reiterating the administration's commitment to ensuring the success of every small-business owner in the country.